---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Guides | hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com';
const description = 'In-depth guides on hospital bill negotiation: how to negotiate, financial assistance programs, billing error correction, and common misconceptions.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Guides</h1>
  <p>Plain-language guides written and reviewed by our editorial team covering the key topics in hospital bill negotiation. Each guide goes beyond the calculator to explain the underlying concepts, legal requirements, and practical steps.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/how-to-negotiate-hospital-bills">How to Negotiate Hospital Bills</a></h3>
  <p>A step-by-step walkthrough of the hospital bill negotiation process — from requesting the itemized bill through applying for financial assistance, disputing errors, and negotiating a lump-sum settlement. Includes what to say, what to document, and what to do when the billing department doesn't cooperate.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/hospital-financial-assistance">Hospital Financial Assistance Programs</a></h3>
  <p>How charity care works under the ACA's Section 501(r) requirements, what income thresholds look like at different types of hospitals, how to find and complete the financial assistance application, and what to do if your application is denied.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/medical-billing-errors">Finding and Fixing Medical Billing Errors</a></h3>
  <p>Medical billing errors affect an estimated 40–80% of hospital bills. This guide explains how to read an Explanation of Benefits, what types of errors are most common, how to write an effective billing dispute, and when to involve your insurer.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/hospital-bill-misconceptions">Common Hospital Bill Misconceptions</a></h3>
  <p>The five most common misunderstandings about hospital bills — why the chargemaster rate is not a fixed price, what "amounts generally billed" means for uninsured patients, who actually qualifies for financial assistance, how medical debt and credit reporting interact, and why waiting to negotiate is almost always the wrong strategy.</p>

  <ul style="margin-top:2rem">
    <li><a href="/case-types">Types of hospital bill negotiations</a></li>
    <li><a href="/methodology">Calculator methodology</a></li>
    <li><a href="/faq">Frequently asked questions</a></li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
